<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call passes PAGE (a static string literal or const char[] buffer) to MHD_create_response_from_buffer_static whose second parameter in common libmicrohttpd APIs is a non-const pointer (void * / char *). This discards the const qualifier of the buffer and therefore fails to use a const-qualified pointer when possible (the API should accept const void *). Hence Rule 8.13 is violated in this scenario.
</scenario>
